Actually, it is a Browning M2 .50cal. There are several indicators of this. First is the size of the cartridges hanging from the feed port. These are clearly .50BMG and not .30-06 or 8mm. The spade grips are common to the .50cal series Brownings, but not in its smaller cousins. Additionally, the front and rear sights are those of the 50cal family. The .30 caliber versions featured a rear leaf site and a folding front site. The size of the buffer (the cylinder located between the spade grips) indicates of that this is an M2 .50 and not an M3.
Actually the markings ( and color of gold rather than older Phantom drone standard trim) indicate this is the most current version of the Phantom 3 – the Phantom “3” Drone
